@startuml

title Mint Username — Welcome Page Flow

actor User
participant "welcome.tsx" as WP
participant "useChainHandle" as UCH
participant "directHandle" as DH
participant "Wallet" as Wallet
participant "Anvil Chain" as Chain
participant "registry-api" as RegAPI
participant "Worker :8788" as Worker
participant "auth/refresh" as Auth
participant "Webapp D1" as D1
participant "authStore" as Store

== 0. Page Load ==

User -> WP: navigate to /welcome
WP -> Store: read me?.username
Store --> WP: me.username (any value)
WP --> User: show welcome form\n(no auto-redirect)

== 1. Username Check (debounced typing) ==

User -> WP: types "kang"
WP -> RegAPI: checkUsernameAvailability("kang", 31337)
RegAPI -> Worker: POST /CheckUsername
Worker -> Worker: SELECT duker_users\nWHERE username = ?
Worker --> RegAPI: {available: true}
WP --> User: "kang.31337 is available"

== 2. Mint — Happy Path ==

User -> WP: clicks "Mint"
WP -> UCH: dispatch(txData)
UCH -> DH: directHandle(txData)
DH -> Wallet: approve USDT
User -> Wallet: confirms
DH -> Wallet: mintUsername("kang", ...)
User -> Wallet: confirms
Wallet --> DH: txHash
DH --> UCH: {txHash}

UCH -> Chain: waitForTransactionReceipt(txHash)
Chain --> UCH: receipt.status = "success"

UCH -> RegAPI: notifyRegistryWorker(txHash, chainId)
RegAPI -> Worker: POST /NotifyDukerTx
Worker -> Chain: getTransactionReceipt
Chain --> Worker: receipt + logs
Worker -> Worker: INSERT duker_users
Worker --> RegAPI: {events, latestEvtSeq}

UCH -> Auth: POST /api/auth/refresh
Auth -> Worker: getRegistryIdentity(addr, eid)\n(via vite proxy /worker-api)
Worker --> Auth: {username: "kang"}
Auth -> D1: UPSERT users SET username="kang"
Auth -> Auth: re-sign JWT
Auth --> UCH: {success, data}

UCH --> WP: {authResult}
WP -> Store: setMe({username: "kang"})
WP --> User: shows success\nuser navigates away manually

== 3. Mint — AlreadyHasIdentity Recovery ==

note over WP
  Wallet has on-chain identity
  but webapp JWT has no username
  (fresh browser, cleared cookies)
end note

User -> WP: clicks "Mint"
WP -> UCH: dispatch(txData)
UCH -> DH: directHandle(txData)
DH -> Wallet: mintUsername(...)
User -> Wallet: confirms
Wallet --> DH: txHash

UCH -> Chain: waitForTransactionReceipt(txHash)
Chain --> UCH: receipt.status = "reverted"
UCH -> UCH: throw "AlreadyHasIdentity"

UCH -> UCH: catch: detect AlreadyHasIdentity
UCH -> RegAPI: syncDukerEvents(chainId)
RegAPI -> Worker: POST /SyncDukerEvents
Worker -> Chain: eth_getLogs(DukerEvent)
Worker -> Worker: upsert duker_users
Worker --> RegAPI: {syncedUpTo}

UCH -> Auth: POST /api/auth/refresh
Auth -> Worker: getRegistryIdentity(addr, eid)\n(via vite proxy /worker-api)
Worker --> Auth: {username: "kang"}
Auth -> D1: UPSERT users SET username="kang"
Auth -> Auth: re-sign JWT
Auth --> UCH: {success, data}

UCH --> WP: {authResult}
WP -> Store: setMe({username: "kang"})
WP --> User: recovery success\nuser navigates away manually

== 4. Subsequent Login ==

User -> WP: SIWE sign-in
WP -> Auth: POST /api/auth/login
Auth -> D1: SELECT username\nWHERE address = ?
D1 --> Auth: username = "kang"
Auth -> Auth: sign JWT with username
Auth --> WP: {username: "kang"}
WP --> User: logged in with username

@enduml
